{"comments":"Keyframe interpolation types for motion graphics.\n\nDefines how values transition between keyframes:\n- Temporal interpolation: timing curves (linear, bezier, easing presets)\n- Spatial interpolation: position path tangents for motion paths\n\n## Architecture\n\nThis module mirrors `Lattice.Animation.FullInterpolationType` from the\nLattice Haskell backend. It works with `Hydrogen.Schema.Motion.Easing`\nfor the actual curve evaluation.\n\n## Usage\n\n```purescript\nimport Hydrogen.Schema.Motion.Interpolation as Interp\n\n-- Linear interpolation (no easing)\nlinear = Interp.fitLinear\n\n-- Ease-in-out cubic\nsmooth = Interp.fitEaseInOutCubic\n\n-- Check if it's a base type\nInterp.isBaseInterpolation linear  -- true\nInterp.isBaseInterpolation smooth  -- false\n```\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[142,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Motion/Interpolation.purs","start":[142,3]},"title":"FITLinear"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[143,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Motion/Interpolation.purs","start":[143,3]},"title":"FITBezier"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[144,12],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Motion/Interpolation.purs","start":[144,3]},"title":"FITHold"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[147,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Motion/Interpolation.purs","start":[147,3]},"title":"FITEaseInSine"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[148,19],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Motion/Interpolation.purs","start":[148,3]},"title":"FITEaseOutSine"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[149,21],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Sc